gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 135, Celtics 102
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Celtics, 135-102. Bobby Portis recorded 28 points, 12 rebounds and a season-high five 3PM for the Bucks, while Giannis Antetokounmpo added 24 points, 12 rebounds and six assists in the victory. Payton Pritchard tallied 21 points, four rebounds and four assists for the Celtics in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 26-12 on the season, while the Celtics fall to 29-9.
